==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inconsequent
<hw>In*con"se*quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inconsequens</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incons⟦eacute⟧quent</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Consequent</er>.]</ety> <def>Not following
from the premises; not regularly inferred; invalid; not characterized by
logical method; illogical; arbitrary; inconsistent; of no
consequence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Loose and <qex>inconsequent</qex> conjectures.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inconsequential</ent>⟦br⟧
